Yes. Because I use GnuWin32 (which has its bin folder in my PATH) I prefer =
not to put C:\cygwin\bin in my PATH but symlink through the required utilit=
ies in C:\Dev\OCaml\bin (C:\Dev\OCaml is my installation root for OCaml) - =
my OCaml installation requires bash.exe (for ocamlbuild), cpp.exe (for ocam=
lnet) and i686-w64-mingw32-ar.exe + i686-w64-mingw32-as.exe + i686-w64-ming=
w32-dlltool.exe + i686-w64-mingw32-gcc.exe + i686-w64-mingw32-ranlib.exe fo=
r ocamlopt.

